\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The two of them farmed legumes, mainly stipple beans, broad beans, and the like. Mandri would give the beans to a woman in Meskalim, who would then smash them up to make a variety of curds. She\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d sell the little curd-bricks and crunchy curd-skins, and she would give Mandri a share of the profit. It was never enough to buy both burgeons and food, so Mandri went hungry. Gil ate grass.}
